file: /cmds/mortal/acopy.c
keywords: mortal, color, ansivars, setcolor, aset
aliases: 
short: ACopy - ANSI Variable Copy
header: Topic: ANSI Copy

  SYNTAX:  acopy <who> <<ansivar> | all>

This command allows you to copy the ANSI variables from one of your own
alternate characters to yourself. You cannot copy variables from another
player that isn't one of your alts. This copy includes both the prefix,
suffix, and whether you have it set to default, partial, or full coloring.

The syntax allows for two options:

acopy <who> <ansivar> - Copies *only* <ansivar> from <who>.
  NOTE: This copies the prefix, suffix, and partial setting. You cannot
        specify just the prefix or suffix using this command.

acopy <who> <all> - Copies *all* ansivars from <who>.

It is important to note that regardless of which format you use, it will
not copy guild ANSI unless *both* characters are in that guild. This is
to help prevent having to store ANSI for guilds that a character is not in.


