header: Topic:  Auto Dispose
syntax: autodispose <item|-item>

The autodispose command will let you set a list of items you wish to
automatically dispose any time you pick them up via the get all command.
This will not affect things which you get manually, are given to you,
etc, these items will only be disposed when you pick them up via
get all.

Examples:
    autodispose gloves

The above line will automatically dispose ALL of the gloves that you
attempt to pick up via get all.

    autodispose -gloves

Adding a - before the item name will remove it from the list.

Typing autodispose without any arguments will display your current list.

NOTE: items which were accidentally disposed of via this mechanic will
not be reimbursed!  Use at your own risk!


