file: /cmds/mortal/botcheck.c
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
 Command: botcheck <person/SHOW/key>
 e.g.:  botcheck rastafan
        botcheck ab+5!y

So, it's the middle of the night, and someone has stolen your kill
for the eleventieth time and is not responding to tells.  You're
almost certain they're botting but no wizards are around (amirite?)
This is your chance to have it checked yourself.  You can 'botcheck'
another player.  If they FAIL that botcheck, you can be sure the
wizards have noticed and will intervene.  However, if they are just
ignoring you and not botting, you'll get the talking to for being
impatient and/or annoying.

If you've been botchecked, you can make it go away by typing the
keyword that's been shown to you using 'botcheck <keyword>'
Someone cannot be botchecked when already botchecked.
You cannot botcheck more often than every 20 minutes.
If botchecked, you have 15 minutes to do something about it.
If you cannot read your keyword, you can 'botcheck SHOW' to have it
displayed again, differently.

The keyword has no uppercase characters in it, even if it looks like it.

You should really try to validate, through tells or other means, if a
person really isn't around before using this command.  Although the
command is anonymous to the receiver, you are logged for the wizards.
A botcheck is received as a 'tell' and does show up in your tell history.

