file: /cmds/mortal/brief.c
keywords: mortal, movement, look, glance
aliases: 
short: Adjusts your brief/mapping exploration settings
header: Topic: Brief

  SYNTAX:  brief

This command allows you to choose what you see as you walk around 3Kingdoms.
There are two facets to this command, brief and mapping...

Brief   : Controls whether you see the Short (one-liner) or Long (verbose)
on/off    descriptions of rooms.

Mapping : Controls whether or not you see the cardinal minimap.  This map
yes/no    is displayed in the right side of your screen and starts out as
          a basic display of exits from your current room.  As you gain
          more skill in cartography ('help adventuring.cartography'), this
          automated minimap becomes much more useful, showing surrounding
          rooms, exits and even monsters and other players in the vicinity.
          You should also check out 'help lineofsight' for more creamy
          mapping goodness.

To adjust your pesonal settings, choose one of the following...
  'brief'          - displays your current brief settings
  'brief on yes'   - brief mode on, yes show the mapping
  'brief off yes'  - brief mode off, yes show the mapping
  'brief on no'    - brief mode on, no don't show the mapping
  'brief off no'   - brief mode off, no don't show the mapping

Note: Regardless of your brief setting, you can still always look at
      the long description of a room via the 'look' command.  Whether
      or not you see the minimap at this time will depend on your
      mapping setting being yes or no.

Note: Regardless of your brief setting, monsters, players and objects
      in the room will still be displayed.

Note: Be careful when exploring new areas in brief mode, you will most
      likely miss many interesting (and potentially dangerous) things.


