file: /cmds/mortal/coins.c
keywords: VAF, funds, basic, mortal, sc, score
aliases: coin, coins, bank, currency, cash, money
short: The status of 3K's mud economy
header: Topic:  Coins and Money
syntax: coins

The standard currency in the three kingdoms (and newbieland) is the
gold coin.  All of the major shops across the lands will gladly take
it, and reluctantly give it back when you sell items.  When you die,
all of the coins you were carrying are left with your corpse.  Thus
as you accumulate coins, you may wish to store some in the bank.  For
more information on the banking system, visit the main bank just north
of the center of town.

As of February, 03, 1999, it was finally agreed by the admin that
the state of money on this mud had become absurd.  Players
were walking around with over a hundred MILLION coins.  A
lot of players have 10s of millions of coins.  This pretty
much blows a hole in any possible mud economy.

Now, here's the sticky part.  Logic doesn't fit all that well
in every aspect of a mud.  But here's one spot that we felt
was a necessary addition (at least to a point).  Money now
has a weight to it.  This means to carry a large sum of
coins you're going to have to give up carrying some other items.
To carry more money, you can buy money bags at a bank.
These will hold a lot of coins, offsetting the weight a bit.

The largest impact that was made is that banks now have a maximum
account balance.  100 million coins in a bank account is silly,
no banker in his right mind wouldn't steal that and leave town.
The bank account maximum for all players is 10,000 coins times that
player's level.  On top of this, high mortals may store an extra 
250,000 coins in their bank accounts.  People who offer 3K voluntary 
access fees may be entitled to a greater bank account maximum.

For you guilds that are MONEY dependent (cybers for instance),
your guild GMs will provide additional means of storing and or
amassing coins for wares and similar necessities.  The rest of
you are going to have to make do.

Addendum:  Several months after the money change, the quantities of
           money have reduced to respectable levels.  Therefore, the
           ADMIN have decided to slowly increase the maximum.  The max
           will never allow the same ridiculous levels as before, but it
           will slowly increase every week.  Use the "balance" command
           at an ATM to check your personal limit.

The 'coins' command will show you how many coins you are currently
carrying on you, and how many coins you have in the bank.  If you have
any means of carrying additional coins from your guild, those will not
show up.

Incidentally, the size of a pile of gold coins logically increases as
the number of coins in it increases.  Below we list for you the basic
progression for the more common coin amounts -- if you find anything
that is not listed, you have found quite a fortune indeed!

A single gold coin.
A couple gold coins.
A few gold coins.
A bunch of gold coins.
A tiny stack of gold coins.
A small pile of gold coins.
A pile of gold coins.
A large pile of gold coins.
A really large pile of gold coins.
A humongous pile of gold coins.

Because so many players have inquired, we will state it herein:    you
are able to 'drop <#> coins' to free some carrying capacity.


