short: Feedback Chat
header: Topic: Feedback Chat

  SYNTAX: fbchat <message>

The 'fbchat' command lets you access a mudwide chatline when wizards
indicate that they are interested in soliciting feedback regarding a
particular topic.  This line is *only* active when a wizard is actively
soliciting feedback.

It is strongly encouraged to stay on the topic as described by the wizard.
Any attempt to bring up another topic is only distracting, no matter how
important you think it is.  If it's a critical bug, please contact the
wizard staff directly.

Feedback Line Commands:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    fbchat <-t>         : display the topic of discussion
    fbchat <who|-w>     : show whos listening to the feedback channel
    fbchat <block|-b>   : toggle blocking of the feedback channel
    fbchat <history|-h> : history of the feedback channel

Wizard Feedback Line Commands:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    fbchat -start <topic> : Start feedback discussion on the specified topic
    fbchat -stop [msg]    : Stop feedback with the optional goodbye message
    fbchat -force <msg>   : Force a comment through, even if no topic is set

TITLED Feedback Line Commands:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    fbchat -ban <who> <reason> : Ban a player from the feedback line
    fbchat -unban <who>        : Remove a ban from a player
    fbchat -whobanned          : List all banned players online


