short: Line of Sight
header: Command: lineofsight
Coupled with a cartography skill of 3, this command allows you to see
surrounding rooms within your current line-of-sight.  Rooms (O) are shown
in a bird's eye mapping format with corresponding exits (^ = up, v = down,
+ = up+down, E = enter) as well as any players, monsters or npcs that may
happen to be in the area (not including your current room).  Your current
room appears as @ unless it has one of the specific exits noted above,
which will appear in yellow.

Even with lower cartography skills ('help adventuring.cartography') you
are able to passively view the cardinal minimap for each room you
encounter.  To fully utilize the ability while exploring (i.e. 'look'ing
or via the passive viewing of the long description of a room) you need
to have mapping enabled in your 'brief' settings ('help brief').
Also, typing 'lineofsight brief' will manually display the minimap.

Be aware that regardless of your skill level, some areas (?) and/or creatures
will be unable to be sighted, particularly guild followers.  Additionally,
assuming you have a light source, dark rooms (#) are viewable along your
line of sight, but you will find that the further the peer into the
darkness, the more powerful of a light source you will need to have.


