header: Command: Nolife

   Syntax:	nolife <player|ranking>

The Nolife list actually shows the players on 3K that need to
get a life (as a result of playing too much).  The list only
shows time for the past two weeks, and is updated every so
often after a player logs off.  Wizards are not included on
the nolife list, only players.  The usage is as following:

'nolife'
'nolife <number>'
'nolife <name>'


Typing 'nolife' alone will show the top ten nolife players.

Typing 'nolife 40' would show you the top 10 and 36-43 nolife players.

Typing 'nolife zorak' would show you the top ten nolife
players, the 4 nolife slots 'above' Zorak, Zorak's
nolife slot, and the 3 nolife slots 'below' Zorak.
(You have to use the lowercase version of someone's name,
 such as 'zorak' and not 'Zorak', or else it will not
 work properly.)


At the bottom after the listing, various things are listed
as follows:

Total Time:
   This is the total time spent online by all the people on
    the nolife list and is calculated periodically.

Fictional Earnings:
   The earnings that the mud would make if they charged
    for connection fees.  First is how much money per
    month, and the second is if they charged however
    much per hour.

Mean Time:
   This is the average time spent online for each player
    on the nolife list for the nolife period.

Total Active Players:
   This shows the number of players that are on the nolife
    list (basically, how many have logged on within the
    period of the past two weeks).

Avg non-idle players:
   This is the average number of active players that have been on
    at the same time within the nolife period.


Once again, the nolife period is the past two weeks.

Users that have not logged on and logged off in the nolife
period of two weeks will not be included in any of these
calculations on the nolife list.

