file: /cmds/mortal/pabvote.c
keywords: mortal, pab
short: Vote for Player Advisory Board
header: Command: pabvote

     Syntax:  pabvote <who>

The pabvote command will allow you to cast a vote for another player to
join the Player Advisory Board. Each physical human player may cast one
vote. You may not vote for yourself. Votes are tracked by the user ID
so if a player has multiple alts, votes for *any* of their characters
will be counted together for that user. For example, if the real life
person, Bob, has three characters, Winkum (main), Blinkum (alt), and Nod
(alt), and the players cast 3 votes for Winkum, 2 for Blinkum, and none
for Nod, the system will tally that as 5 votes for Winkum (as that is
Bob's main).

Once voting has ended, the wizards will view the results and the top two
(2) winners, subject to veto by the Archons, will be appointed to their
roles along with one (1) picked by the Solar staff, and one (1) picked
by the Archons. The term shall last for one (1) year. If a board member
elects to step down or refuses to serve, the next person on the voting
list shall be chosen, as the list is retained until the next vote.

Anyone caught trying to circumvent the system to vote more than once by
any means will be wiped. No questions asked. So don't even think about
trying to 'test' it.


