short:  Will I die here??
header: Topic: Rating

  SYNTAX: rating [autorating off/on]

The 'rating' command will give you an area rating based upon
a general minimum recommended level for an area, and your player
level.  Please note that two players of different levels, standing
in the same room, will receive a different rating for that area.
This command gives you the area name, a rough idea of the levels
it was targetted to, and a class range of monsters found in the
area.  Furthermore, with the 'rating' vaf perk it will also show
how many rooms have been discovered in the area, whether or not the
room you're standing in normally starts with a monster, and
if you can acquire a unique item in this room.
The 'rating' command is usually a manual command, to be entered by
you when curious about an area.  However, new characters start in
a mode called 'autorating' where you will see the rating screen any
time you move from one wizard's area to another.  You can turn this
off (or back on again) using 'rating autorating off'

NOTE:

  The area rating is not a guarantee to avoid death.  As with all
  exploring, there are risks involved.  The rating system should
  ONLY be used as a guide, to help give you an estimate whether
  the area may be too difficult to fight in at your level.  Guild
  powers and levels are not factored into the rating system.

WARNING

  Please use extreme caution when exploring.  You will NOT be
  reimbursed for any deaths caused due to lack of understanding
  the information provided by the rating system.  You have been
  warned.

