file: /cmds/mortal/repeat.c
keywords: mortal, basic, miscellaneous, panic, reflex
aliases: 
short:  Set or show repeat actions
header: Topic: Repeat

  SYNTAX: repeat <when>/<action>/[dur]/[phase]/[notify]

The 'repeat' command allows you to set up an action to occur every
round, every combat round, and/or every non-combat round.
The following options are available:
 action : what command you would like to repeat
 when   : 'always', 'combat', or 'nocombat'
 dur    : for how many rounds, 0 means forever
 phase  : 0 = at the beginning of your round
          1 = at the end of your round
          2 = between your guild's automations but before attacking
          3 = between your guild's automations but after your attacks
          (you will want to tweak this depending on how your guild reacts)
 notify : A message you want displayed when it expires, only valid if
          you've provided a duration

Examples:
 Turn it off:
  repeat combat/off  -- off in combat
  repeat off  -- everything off

 In combat, always cast a spell after my guild has had its first chance to
 intercede in the round:
  repeat combat/cast death face at goblin/0/2

 I'm a cat...:
  repeat always/lick self/10/0/0/You are now clean.

 Combat has ended, repeat 1 time at the beginning of the first round that
 there is no combat:
  repeat nocombat/guildchat I'm not fighting, my bot broke./1/0


