file: /cmds/mortal/reps.c
keywords: mortal, reps, reputation
aliases: 
short: Shows a report of your characters reputations.
header: Topic: Reps

  Syntax: reps [-short] [-p:<who>] [<regexp>]

This command shows you your reputation with various factions in the
game.  Depending on how well liked or hated you are with a particular
group could impact your dealings with them.
The bar graph conveniently provided for you shows your progress within
a given faction.  Further to the left is nearing a more hostile status
while further to the right is nearing a friendlier status.

The '-short' argument will display the output without the graph section.
The '<regexp>' argument will only show factions that match the pattern.
The '-p:<who>' argument will display the reps for player <who>, if online.

Example:

 FACTION LIST :: Yournamehere

 Name                                 Reputation
 -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
 fe dar Shad                          despised      |--*-----------------|
 Pinnacle Tower                       neutral       |----------*---------|

In this example you are despised with 'fe dar Shad' and closer to
being even more hated than you are to being more liked.  Similarly you
are smack dab in the middle of neutral for Pinnacle Tower.

Note: In many cases reputation is used as a point system or currency.  In
      these cases you can partake of your good favor to acquire items
      for free (no coin cost) or nearly free, this will reduce your 
      reputation based on the level of hospitality you've partaken.

