file: /cmds/mortal/scaler.c
Allows you to set the level that your scaling dungeons will apply
when you enter them.  The range is 75% of your level to your level+5

The scaling happens upon your very first entry into a new dungeon,
once set, the scaled level will not change until the dungeon is cleared
from your 'dungeons' list.
For example: Bob, the level 37 thief, is fighting in Puppymill.  All
the puppies are scaled to level 37 because he didn't set his scaler.
Bob sets his scaler to 29, because thieves are worse than gentech,
but his puppies will remain unchanged.  So Bob wanders over to Alphabet
land, which he hasn't been in yet, and it scales to 29.  Bob then
sets his scaler to 39 and heads to Death Taco, which will scale to
level 39.  Now, no matter what Bob does, his Death Taco is set to 39
his Alphabet to 29 and Puppymill to 37.  If Bob clears his dungeons
then when he re-enters, it will scale to his current scaler level

Typing 'scaler' with no argument will tell you what your current
scaler is set to and also the level of the dungeon you're currently in.
(This level shows up on the 'dungeons' command as well.)

