file: /cmds/mortal/spawnchar.c
keywords: spawn, second, character, seconds, multiple, characters
aliases: 
short: Spawnsecond
header: Topic: Second Characters

  SYNTAX: spawnsecond            - lists your additional character statuses
  SYNTAX: spawnsecond <charname> - links up <charname> to your character list
  SYNTAX: spawnsecond toggle     - toggles your chars' visiblity in finger info

Legally spawns an additional character, linking it to your other character(s).
All your current characters must be at least level 50 to do this.  If you don't
have an open slot (type 'spawnsecond' to see if you do), then you can check
out 'help vaf' and 'vaf list xchar' to see how to gain another.

        * * * * * READ THE INSTRUCTIONS CAREFULLY * * * * *

1) Be logged in with your 'main' char (probably the one you're using now)
2) Create (and login) your new character (example: Bob)
3) With both logged in, on your main character, type 'spawnsecond bob'
   (well, not 'bob' but the name of your new character, of course)
4) Logout one of your characters
5) Play on!

With regards to 'spawnsecond toggle,' every character starts out by default
as "not shown".  If you keep it this way, not showing a character, for
instance, "Bob," Bob will not show anyone linked to him in his finger info,
nor will Bob appear in any of your other characters' finger infos.  If you
choose to show Bob, he will appear in all of your other character's finger
infos, except for those that are not themselves being shown.  As an example,
Bob, Steve and Pete are your chars.  You show Bob and Steve.  Finger either
Bob or Steve and you see both in each other's finger info, but Pete is not
shown in either.  Finger Pete and you won't see anyone else in his finger
info either.  Clear as mud?  Great, you'll figure it out.  Also, you can only
toggle a character's showing from that character, while they are logged in.

If you run into any problems, report it to a SOLAR+ IMMEDIATELY.

See 'help acopy' for migrating your ansi variables to your alt(s).

Please see help seconds for more.


