file: /cmds/mortal/wall.c
keywords: friends, friend
aliases: walls
short: All About Walls
header: Walls
syntax: wall <optional arguments>

Walls on 3-Kingdoms are a place where people can share short messages
with their friends and the mud.  Everybody has one, and you can decide
to keep it viewable by the public, or visible by only your friends.

Use this command in conjuntion with others listed at the end of this file.

  ** If your wall is publicly readable by the whole mud, keep
  ** it clean.  Standard public chatline rules apply.
  ** (see 'help rules' if you need to know what these are)

You can post messages to your own wall, and to any of your alternate
characters' walls, and have the power to remove postings from them too.
You can also post to any of your friends' walls.

Each message is limited to 280 characters, and each wall is limited
to 10 messages.  Adding a new message to an already full wall will
simply remove the oldest message on the wall.

wall
  View your character's wall.

wall catchup
  Read any new posts to your friends' walls that you haven't read already.

wall <character OR nickname>
  Read another someone else's wall.

wall <message>
  Post a message to your wall.

wall <character> <message>
  Post a message to another character's wall.  This could be one of your
  other characters, or a friend's character.

wall remove [character] #
  Remove a post from your wall.  If you include a the optional character
  name (and it's one of your characters), remove the message from their
  wall instead.

wall private <character>
  Make one of your characters' walls private to friends only.

wall public <character>
  Make one of your characters' walls publicly readable to all.

wall hidden
  View which of your characters have private walls and public walls.
  This will also show you which characters are hidden and which are
  visible.


