file: /help/!
The character '!' can be prepended to most commands to allow the
command to bypass other things that have focus. For instance, while
you are editing a post on a board, or sending a mail, you can use
the ! before the command to allow it to go through as if you were not
in the editor currently.

For example you can:
  !look

Which, even though you were in the editor, would show you the room
you are currently in.

