file: /help/BASIC/alignment
keywords: general, 
aliases: 
short: The Good, the Bad and the... Neutral?
header: Alignment

  As you play 3 Kingdoms, you will notice that the phrase in parenthesis
  at the end of your title will continually change.  This is a known
  as your alignment.  The alignment is controlled by your actions.  Killing
  many evil monsters and performing righteous deeds will earn you a very
  noble reputation.  The same can be said in the reverse.  The order of
  alignments is listed below from good to evil.  It should be noted that
  not all of the alignments are listed below.  The extremes on both ends
  of the spectrum can only be known by achieving them yourself or being
  present when another player has.  Until then, they are a mystery to
  be solved.  Good luck.

		Good			Evil
	       ******		       ******
		neutral			neutral
		nice			mean
		moral			immoral
		righteous		malicious
		pure			corrupt
		good			evil
		 ?			 ?

Alignment may be important for some guilds, and for the use of 
some objects in the game.  For example, one would not expect an
evil character to be able to wield a "Harp of the Angels".

Type 'help vaf' to learn how to set a custom alignment title.

--------------------
file: /help/BASIC/botting
Unattended Botting is illegal.

Scripting is allowed, as long as you are at your keyboard, and responsive.

Being unresponsive, yet entering commands while unresponsive, is botting
and is not allowed under any circumstance, both under the rules regarding
botting and the rules regarding anti-idle triggers.

If you are checked by a Wizard to see if you are botting, and have not
replied back to them in UNDER 15 MINUTES, bad things can happen.

To be clear you are expected to:

  1) Set a Deadman - If a Wizard botchecks you, you usually
     have about 15 minutes before you're in trouble. If you
     cannot be bothered to look at a game you're "playing"
     every 15 minutes or so, why are you here?
  2) Answer Botchecks - If you are getting messages from a
     Wizard, please answer them. Even if it's nothing but a
     "Yeah, I'm here, please no smite." If we are sending
     messages, that means you are on our radar.
  3) Know The Rules - "help rules" exists for a reason.
     Know them.

Punishments are structured and progress with each successive time
you are caught breaking the rules related to botting. They are as
follows:

  1) Warning - Hey, your bot is bad. Fix it. Please stop botting.
  2) Deaths - Hey, here's some deaths, and some Jailtime!
  3) Removal From Your Guild - Removed from your guild, and banned
     from re-joining it.
  4) Deletion Of Your Character


Please, read 'help rules'.
They are there for a reason.

