The 'history' command will give you a list of the 128 most recent
commands you have typed in.  With the optional argument,
you may elect to list fewer than the default 128 commands.

The last 128 commands that you type in will be stored in a buffer
for you to look at and use.  Any command started with the percent
sign is treated as a history command.

