file: /help/CMDS/arealist
keywords: mortal, area, areas, list, alist
aliases: 
short: Listing of areas
header: Command: Arealist

   SYNTAX: arealist <number|id|by:name|of:realm|fixer:name|
           -fixed|-unfixed|-checked|-unchecked>

'arealist' with no arguments will list all the areas in the game.

Options are:
	<number/id>	: more details of the area with that number, or id.
	of:<realm>	: areas belonging to the specified realm.
	by:<name>	: areas coded by the wizard <name>.
	-closed		: areas that are temporarily closed.
	-defunct	: areas that are closed for good.
	fixer:<name>	: areas that have been fixed for the new AC/WC values
	            	  by the wizard <name>.
	-fixed		: areas fixed for the new WC/AC values.
	-unfixed	: areas that aren't fixed for the new WC/AC values.
	-checked	: 'fixed' areas that have been checked and approved
	        	  (by Alayna or some other higher power).
	-unchecked	: 'fixed' areas that have not been checked and approved
	          	  yet.

You can also combine args, eg:

'arealist of:chaos by:mischief -unfixed' would list all areas in
Chaos that were coded by Mischief and aren't yet fixed.

'id' can match anything from the area's name, realm or coders or
unique id. eg. 'arealist cave' would list any areas with the string
'cave' in their name, while 'arealist mos' would list anything coded
by Mosiah, or Mos, or anything that happened to have 'mos' somewhere
in its name.


