file: /help/CMDS/save
keywords: mortal, score, miscellaneous
aliases: 
short: How to have 'score' be there again for you when you relog
header: Topic: Save

  SYNTAX:  save

  The save command takes your stats (which include your strength,
dexterity, experience, age, quest info you used, etc.) and places
them all on the mud hard drive for future reference. This future
reference is usually when you log on again the next day.
  Fortunately for you, you are saved automaticly every 15 minutes,
when you quit and (unfortunately) when you die (no way to weasel out
of that unpleasant experience).

  For those who wonder why this command even exists. Well, if the mud was
pink and there were no wizzes or random force of nature then this command
would have been obsolete and I wouldn't have told you about all this.
  But life is not as such, and accidents (and "accidents") do happen that
cause the mud to crash unexpectingly causing all information of you
between the last save to the present moment to be completely lost and
there will be no proof that you actually did kill cancer.
  So sometimes it is wise to follow the advice I give when I start coding:
             "Save now, and save often!"


