keywords: mortal, basic, look, examine
aliases: 
short: How to find king solomons lost treasure
header: Command: Search
::::::::::::::::::::::
    Topic: search
::::::::::::::::::::::

  Syntax:  search
   OR:   search <item>

You are in a mysterious room and you have a gut feeling that there is
more here than meets the eye. So to confirm or disperse your suspecions
you search.
If you do it in the general form 'search' then in other words, you look
around aimlessly, giving each item in the room a little attention, hoping
that something will jump up and grab your ass.
If you choose a more specific form (i.e.: 'search table') then you give
the table your utmost attention trying to find the thinnest of clues
(this search sometimes end up with an anal probe).

If your treasure.gemology skill is trained you will be able to
occasionally find gems in otherwise empty rooms.  Sure, it
might be tedious to search every room you come to, but for the
chance at that rare diamond, isn't it worth it?
Note: If a gem is not found on the first search by the first person
      with gemology, that means no gem exists in that room. (for anyone)


