file: /help/SOUL/soul
keywords: feelings, soulhist, trs, newsoul
aliases: souls
short: Soul Commands & Information
header: Souls

Souls not only allows you to express your feelings in the present room, but
also to other players across the mud, or even other realms of the 3Kingdoms
universe.  There are also features that allow you to express your feelings
to everyone in the current room.  For example, to hug everyone in the room,
just type 'hug all' rather than typing in each name individually.

  help soul       - This screen
  help feelings   - More help on the soul
  <feeling> all   - Express <feeling> to everyone in room
  trs             - help trs for more
  soulhist        - recalls the last 15 feelings done to you (help soulhist)
  soul <letter>   - lists all feelings beginning with <letter>
  newsoul <idea>  - submits an <idea> for a new feeling
  soulnew         - lists new feelings within the last two weeks
  soulnew <#>     - lists new feelings within the last <#> days
  soul off        - temporarily disables all your feelings
                    This is handy if you suspect that a soul emote is
                    conflicting with another action
  soul on         - guess

To send souls across different realms, use the @ symbol.
For example: 'grin barnaby@3s'


