 blood matches due to any player witnessed 'BSness', to a point.  After that
 point, blood matches become in jeopardy of becoming extinct, players are in
 jeopardy of being wiped, etc...  NO GOOD will come of any bitching, it
 will never get a guild power reduced, it will never get a player banned.
 And it is even possible that your character will be demoted or removed if
 you do bitch.

 Keep in mind, the 'point' at which bitching becomes an issue is completely
 arbitrary and up to the powers that be.  So don't push your luck.

 The point of blood matches is to be fun for everyone, not just you.  If you
 got killed, so be it.  We don't want to hear about it.  I can't stress this
 point enough.  If you start bitching about guilds, or powers, or players
 because of things that happened in an blood match, we will be majorly pissed.

 If you think a bug was abused, you better be DAMN sure it was a bug
 before you come complaining.


 Update: 5/30/99
 A new thing has been introduced, a TEAM blood match.  It's very similar
 to a real blood match except that the last TEAM alive is the winner.
 If you're on the winning team (even if you died!) you'll get the
 recognition and part of the prize (coins) for winning.
 In team blood matches you do NOT get to pick your team, the teams
 are built randomly based on level to make them relatively equal.

 There are a few key players in a team blood match:
  LEADER - This is the leader of each team.  This person carries the
           team leader horn.  This horn can be blown to summon all
           of the team members to the leaders' location.  It can
           also be waved to heal the entire team to full.  Each power can be
           used only once.
  FROG   - This is basically the 'second in command' on each team, the
           second highest player.  This person carries the PIGWAD
           (Portable Inter-Galactic Wormhole Activation Device) and
           he/she can use that device to step through a wormhole to any
           of his teammates.  This device has roughly 7 charges.
  SAFETY - This person carries a scroll of resurrection that can only be
           used on the team leader of his/her team.  If the safety outlives
           the team leader, this scroll can be used to bring the leader back.

  All players less than level 30 receive the BONG OF CHAOS.  This wondrous
  device can be 'toked' for a good sized heal, and possibly over max hp/sp.
  It has limited charges, so finding WHEN to use it is the key factor.



