file: /help/formulas
keywords: general, player
aliases: calculating
short: What formulas are in use by the mud
heading: MUD Formulas

The following guild formulas are available for you to study.  Please
help us remember to update this if formulas have changed since the last
update date listed below.

The first formula is...
Armor Class has two settings, a high and a low.  These determine the min
and max blocking for a piece of armor.  The default settings are that
the min is 10% of the max.  So an "AC90" main is really a 90/9.
(Note that fractions are rounded.  AC85 max has a min of 9 also.)
Wizards can code armors with higher minimums, or larger spans, and
also some guild powers can impact them.
The minimum is always blocked and the max is randomly determined by the
span between the low and high.

Effect of Armor resistances:
 damage_blocked = low_ac + random(1 + AC - low_ac)
 e.g.  damage_blocked = 9 + random(1 + 90 - 9);
 - Penetration attacks ignore AC
 - Your guild MIGHT interfere with damage before AC is applied (uncommon)

ACs are impacted by skills at the player level:
 + 1% to max AC per skill point, +1 to low AC per skp.
 e.g. Overall I have a 350/35 AC.  I train my "power" skill (radiation)
      to 5, I would gain 5% (17) max AC, and 5 to min AC.



Last  Updated: 2017/03/29

