file: /help/icotag
keywords: general, boons, icotag
aliases:
short: Icotag Boon
heading: boons

  SYNTAX:  icotag <item>

This command is only provided as a boon by the wizards.  When it is,
you can 'icotag' an item to stay with you after you quit.  It's fairly
limited, so make sure you understand:
1) Once icotag'd, an item will only load within 10 minutes after you quit
2) If you lose the item before you quit (or before reboot), it will
   not return.
3) Unique items will not spawn duplicates if icotag'd.
4) An icotag'd item will appear at the bottom of your inventory list
   when you return.
5) Not all items can be icotagged.  The list of exceptions and reasons
   are too numerous, but 90% of content IS taggable.
6) If you go LD right before boot, you will likely be forced
   to quit and all your items sold at Cancer right before
   reboot, causing you to run up against #2 above. So do not
   go LD right before boot and expect icotag to work.


