file: /help/idle
keywords: general, linkdeath
aliases: idling
short: What happens when you do absolutely nothing
heading: Idle

  SYNTAX:  idle <player name>

The 'idle' command will show you how long another player has been idle.

When you are idle for roughly 5 minutes, you cease to age.
Shortly thereafter, you will no longer be eligible to receive
experience or to fight in combat.

Wizards may remain idle until the reboot.

Players may remain idle for TWO hours until linkdeath.
Type 'help vaf' to learn how to increase this to up to EIGHT hours
by selecting the idle perk.

Note that there are other methods of determining if players are idle,
it often appears on finger, mywho, or guild listings.

