file: /help/polls
keywords: poll, pvote
aliases:
short: Player submitted polling system
header: 3-Kingdoms Polling System

The polling system provides you an opportunity to post polls or vote on
the polls of others.  Polls may be registered in the Poll Room in
Pinnacle for a fee.  This fee may change so be sure to check the sign
in the Poll Room before registering.  The following poll types are
available for use:

Bootpolls:
---------
These run for most of an entire boot and only one may be run each boot.
If a bootpoll is running a second may be queued to run after the next
reboot.  Bootpolls close 45 minutes before reboot, so keep this in
mind if you want your poll to run for a while and it is getting near
reboot time.  A poll posted after this closing time will be queued to
run 15 minutes after reboot, so long as there is not already a bootpoll
waiting to be run.

Quickpolls:
----------
These run for 5 minutes, and the system supports the queuing of one
quickpoll while another is running.  The last quickpoll may be run 11
minutes before reboot, after which registration will result in the
poll being run approximately 15 minutes after reboot.

During the time when a poll is running, a chat line is open on which to
discuss it. See 'help poll' for more information on the line.

See 'help pvote' for information on voting on the running polls
and checking recent polls results.

PLEASE NOTE: You are responsible for the following rules as well as
for those outlined in 'help poll' for the chat line.  Normal rules
from 'help rules' do, of course, apply.

RULES FOR POSTING POLLS:

1) Consider polls to have the same language usage rules as the shout line.

2) You my NOT use the polling system to harass or denigrate another player.
   It is generally advisable to leave references to players and wizards 
   out of the polls.

3) The polling system is not a venue for lodging complaints.  This
   includes whining about things such as guild balance or PK.  There
   are better venues for such complaints, and polls should be kept
   to fun or interesting topics.

Failure to heed these rules will result in being temporarily or permanently
banned from registering new polls and/or using the chat line.

