file: /help/seconds
keywords: general, rules, punishment, register, quest, highmortal, spawnsecond, milestones
aliases: seconds, characters, thirds, multiple
short: Multiple Characters
header: Multiple Characters
Multiple characters (played by the same human) on 3K are ILLEGAL until
you reach level 50, at which point you are allowed one extra character
which MUST BE REGISTERED using the 'spawnsecond' command.

Once both your first and legal second characters have reached level 50
you are allowed a legal third. This too must be registered using the
spawnsecond command.  Beyond this, if any of your characters get to level
100, you receive one more additional char, for a maximum of four total.

Type 'help vaf' to learn about the xchar perk ('vaf xchar')
which allows you to gain an unlimited number of additional characters
regardless of the levels any have attained.

To assist you registering, please read 'help spawnsecond'

Keep in mind that only your primary character, the original one,
can use the spawnsecond command. 
  
Standard punishment for dealing with illegal characters is removal of
(at least) the highest level character.  Often times, abuse will cause
all to be removed.  Similarly, if you have an additional character that
is not registered, it will be dealt with as above.

Login of multiple characters within the same reboot follows the below rules:
 
  1) You cannot login a character when the an "other" is already logged in.
     I.e. You can swap them out freely, but not play them at the same time
  2) Linkdead characters are considered to be "logged in"

  Type 'vaf ldlogin' to learn how you can circumvent rule 2) above 
 
Some standard rules about your other characters:

 * Other players will not know if you have multiple characters, but
   all titled wizards do.  So don't screw around.  Anything that one of
   your multiple characters does can be used against your main character,
   especially bug abuse, harassment, etc.  Most likely, the highest of
   your characters will be dealt punishment, and the lowest wiped.
   You may even lose your privilege of having multiple characters, ever.

 * Along with the above rule, nobody has the right to ever ask you
   who your other characters are.  A titled wizard will never ask
   because they can already find it out for themselves.  Nobody else
   can, so nobody else can ask.

   Note: This protection doesn't mean much if you blab the secret
         to anyone, even friends.  Tell one person and they'll probably let
         it slip somewhere down the road.  Simply put, if you don't want
         people to know your other characters, then don't tell a soul.

 * Clearly, the above points regarding additional character secrecy
   go out the window if you choose to 'spawnsecond toggle' any of them.

 * All rules still apply to your other characters.  This may seem
   obvious but some people need things spelled out for them.

 * There are probably more things, they will be added as we come up
   with them.  Ignorance of the contents of this file is not a valid
   excuse for breaking the rules.

